               <p>I am a <rs id="t17760109-30-viclabel154" type="occupation">goldsmith</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760109-30-victim296 t17760109-30-viclabel154"></join> in <placeName id="t17760109-30-crimeloc155">the Minories</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17760109-30-crimeloc155" type="placeName" value="the Minories"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17760109-30-crimeloc155" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760109-30-off152 t17760109-30-crimeloc155"></join>: on the second of January I heard my glass fly; I run out of the shop, laid hold of the prisoner, and took one of the buckles out of his hand, and the others he dropt privately beside the counter.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Did not you tell me I did not look like a thief, and you did not think I came with an intent to steal the buckles? - I did say so: I am lame; I said so because I wanted him to go about his business; but he said he came on purpose to rob me, and if I did not prosecute him he would prosecute me.</p>

               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I did not go with an intent to steal the buckles; it was one o'clock in the day.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17760109-30-verdict156" type="verdictDescription">
